MODULE: Markets in Financial Instruments (MiFID II / MiFIR)

Directive 2014/65/EU on Markets in Financial Instruments (MiFID II)
Regulation (EU) No 600/2014 on Markets in Financial Instruments (MiFIR)

Description: This framework governs the authorization, organization, and conduct of investment firms and trading venues across the EU/EEA. It establishes rules for how firms provide investment services, 
interact with clients, execute trades, manage conflicts, and ensure market transparency and integrity.

It is the core regime for:

Investment services and activities
Client protection and conduct of business
Market structure and trading obligations

Scope:

Investment services
Client relationships
Trading and execution

Applies When:
- a firm provides investment advice
- a firm executes or transmits orders
- a client relationship exists involving investment services
- portfolio management is performed
- financial instruments are marketed, distributed, or sold
- trading venue or market structure obligations are involved

Key Rules:

Client categorization (Retail / Professional / Eligible Counterparty)
Suitability and appropriateness assessments
Best execution obligations
Product governance (manufacturer and distributor responsibilities)
Conflicts of interest management
Inducements and fee structures
Costs and charges disclosures
Recordkeeping and reporting
Transaction reporting to regulators
Pre- and post-trade transparency


Do Not Apply When:
- no investment service or activity is provided
- communication is purely internal
- no financial instrument or client interaction exists

