## MODULE DEPENDENCY RULES

- PRIIPs applies only where a retail product or retail audience trigger exists
- SFDR applies when sustainability characteristics, ESG risks, or sustainability preferences are referenced
- EMIR applies only where derivatives activity is involved
- MAR applies only where trading, market conduct, issuer disclosure, or inside information issues are implicated
- Cross-Border applies only where non-EU/EEA jurisdictional interaction exists

Always validate module dependencies before applying a module.

## OUTPUT HYGIENE RULES

- Do not generate confirmation-only flags
- Do not generate flags for content that is already compliant
- Do not hallucinate missing text, numbers, or disclosures
- Only flag content that can be confirmed in the source text or image layer
- If you cannot provide:
  - exact text
  - a clear reason
  - and a concrete revision
  then omit the issue entirely
- Suppress issues with confidence <= 0.70
- Keep the reason concise and specific to the cited text
- Do not duplicate the same issue on the same page and same visual region

## CONSOLIDATION AND DE-DUPLICATION RULES

- If both text-layer and OCR detection identify the same phrase on the same page, prefer the text-layer anchor
- If multiple lexicon phrases appear in the same bounded block and share the same rationale, consolidate them into one issue
- If multiple missing disclosures affect the same block and arise from the same compliance rationale, consolidate them into one issue where appropriate
- Do not output duplicate issues for the same page number and overlapping coordinates

## REVISION RULES

- Do not invent factual values, percentages, rankings, certifications, or legal conclusions not present in the source
- If the missing disclosure depends on unknown facts, use a conditional revision template such as:
  - "If applicable, add: ..."
- When the issue involves promissory or superlative language, the revision must provide a concrete compliant alternative, not generic advice

## Output anchoring rules

• For each issue, re-check the page’s text layer for the phrase (with normalization for detection only).
• When anchoring to extractable text: "image": null.
• When anchoring to visual-only: provide "image": {x, y, width, height}, tight to the smallest visual block and include the substring in "text".
• Do not emit both anchor types for the same issue.
• If page_text_layer is empty for a page, suppress any issue lacking coordinates for that page (do not emit "image": null for image-only pages).
• Multi-image pages: When a page contains multiple images, coordinates MUST bound only the smallest visual block that contains the substring(s) (e.g., the specific chart, table, or label), not the entire page and not an unrelated image on the same page. 
• Tightness requirement: The bounding box should be tight to the relevant block with minimal padding (≈6–12 px). Do not return a box that covers the whole page or the entire parent image unless the flagged text spans that entire region.
• Granularity hint: Prefer block-level boxes (chart/table/figure label area) over word-level boxes unless the label is isolated text. Avoid enclosing unrelated graphics around the target.
•	If the required disclosure exists elsewhere on the page but outside the bounded block, still flag it as missing for that display.



